The News Journal's "Hi, I'm in Delaware" pop culture podcast is recorded weekly in the newsroom. (Photo: Ryan Cormier/The News Journal) 
On this week's "Hi, I'm in Delaware!," it's just Ryan Cormier and Sarika Jagtiani in the studio alone, kickin' it old school without a guest. 
The duo discuss Sarika's night at the grand opening of The Fillmore Philadelphia, which featured a sold out show by her beloved Hall & Oates, as well as fall TV and the perils of using builders' foam as hair mousse . 
Plus, they chat about yet another Delaware shout-out on Fox's "Last Man on Earth": A video posted by Ryan Cormier (@ryancormier) on Sep 28, 2015 at 5:53pm PDT 
The podcast closes with a brand new tune called "Halloween" by one of Ryan's favorite Wilmington rock bands, Gozer . The song is from the act's forthcoming new EP. Check them out at Oddity Bar in Wilmington Oct. 17 . 
Press play below in the embedded Soundcloud player to listen to the podcast.
